k shows, is to renew itself conceptually through deep engagement with new forms of aesthetic experience.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aAesthetics. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspects. 4aChristian Metz. 4aGilles Deleuze. 4aHarun Farocki. 4aStanley Cavell. 4aVictor Burgin. 4adigital or virtual images. 4alogic of sensation. 4amemory of cinema. 4amoving image installation. 4aphotography and belief. 70(DE-601)1045596830(DE-588)4017102-4aFilm2gnd 70(DE-601)1058229570(DE-588)4114333-4aKunst2gnd 70(DE-601)1062002590(DE-588)4045791-6aPhilosophie2gnd 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226513225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226513225.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles